Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteInst(25.10)                                            deleteInst(25.10)

Name
       deleteInst - Deletes an instance from a design

Syntax
       deleteInst

       [-help]

       <listOfInst>

       [-moduleBased <moduleName>]

       [-verbose]

       Deletes  an instance from a design. Innovus checks whether the instance
       is physical or logical, and deletes the instance accordingly.  You  can
       use deleteInst to delete the list of logical instances in one HECO ses-
       sion.

       You  can  use wildcards (*?) to specify the instances you want the tool
       to delete.

       As deleteInst supports deletion of a list of instance, you can get  the
       list of instances using the dbGet command  The correct way to use dbGet
       is to use TCL join command. The following example shows the correct us-
       age of deleteInst command with dbGet:

       deleteInst [ join [dbGet top.insts.name]]

       Notes:

              * If  the deleteInst command deletes a constrained instance, the
                command will delete the timing graph to  avoid  other  crashes
                because  constraints would be referring to deleted objects and
                a message will be displayed.

              * The deleteInst command cannot be used in  the  post-mask  ECO.
                Please  use loadECO <ecofile> -postMask to delete instances in
                the post-mask ECO.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deleteInst.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteInst

       <listOfInst>
              Specifies the list of the instances to delete.

       -moduleBased <m><oduleName>
              Specifies the name of the Verilog module.

       -verbose
              Prints out the deleted instance message.

Example
              * The following command deletes instance i1/i2:

                deleteInst i1/i2

              * The  following command deletes all instances whose names begin
                with i inside the hierarchical instance i1:

                deleteInst i1/i*

              * The following command deletes the instance insta from the ver-
                ilog module HIER_2:

                deleteInst -moduleBased HIER_2 insta

              * The following command deletes all instances in the  SPGM  mod-
                ule:

                deleteInst * -moduleBased SPGM

Related Information
              * addInst

              * loadECO

